<programme start="20241220180000 +0000" stop="20241220190000 +0000" channel="AnimalPlanet.ee"><title lang="ee">Pit Bulls &amp; Parolees</title><desc lang="ee">American reality series following the team at the Villalobos Rescue centre on their quest to rescue and rehome dogs. Founded by Tia Maria Torres, the centre challenges the misconceptions surrounding &apos;bully breeds&apos;, such as pit bulls, with hopes of eventually rehoming them. Alongside Tia are her team of dog-loving parolees, each tasked with training, rescuing and caring for the animals. Each episode covers the emotional stories of both her employees and their rescue dogs. Will their jobs help them as they transition away from jail or will they struggle alongside the pups to rebuild their reputation?</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220190000 +0000" stop="20241220200000 +0000" channel="AnimalPlanet.ee"><title lang="ee">Legends Of the Wild</title><desc lang="ee">The natural world is full of tales of mysterious animal attacks on humans and inexplicable sightings of strange and sinister creatures. Wilderness experts Damian Duffy and Matt Hoffman decided to check out these stories for themselves and set off across the globe to investigate the reports. Using their experience and skills as a former army paratrooper (Damian) and an accomplished wildife photographer (Matt) they journey deep into the wild places and risk their lives to uncover the truth.Their investigations take them from the baffling and gory deaths of ranchers in Brazil to the return of a mythical Australian killer to the disappearance of villagers and farm animals in the Philippines and mystifying Alaskan sea creatures.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220200000 +0000" stop="20241220210000 +0000" channel="AnimalPlanet.ee"><title lang="ee">Legends Of the Wild</title><desc lang="ee">The natural world is full of tales of mysterious animal attacks on humans and inexplicable sightings of strange and sinister creatures. Wilderness experts Damian Duffy and Matt Hoffman decided to check out these stories for themselves and set off across the globe to investigate the reports. Using their experience and skills as a former army paratrooper (Damian) and an accomplished wildife photographer (Matt) they journey deep into the wild places and risk their lives to uncover the truth.Their investigations take them from the baffling and gory deaths of ranchers in Brazil to the return of a mythical Australian killer to the disappearance of villagers and farm animals in the Philippines and mystifying Alaskan sea creatures.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220210000 +0000" stop="20241220220000 +0000" channel="AnimalPlanet.ee"><title lang="ee">Edge of Alaska</title><desc lang="ee">McCarthy, Alaska is home to a rugged bunch of mavericks and risk takers, willing to brave the brutal conditions in this icy, isolated town. Once a thriving, prosperous place due to the gold rush, the town is now home to a mere 40 people. There is a juxtaposition between residents; while some believe in a traditional way of life, others are desperate to drag McCarthy into the modern age, believing this is the only way to ensure its survival. Edge of Alaska tells the story of this community at a crossroads.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220220000 +0000" stop="20241220223000 +0000" channel="AnimalPlanet.ee"><title lang="ee">Meet the Orangutans</title><desc lang="ee">Meet the Orangutans is a documentary series set in Borneo, in the first orangutan rehabilitation center, where the staff help these young apes prepare for life in the jungle. Join Sue Sheward and her team, as they take care of orphaned and wounded monkeys, and teach them the basic skills for survival, like tree-climbing, nest-building and finding food. Meet the friendly, fun and often even naughty orangs, as they grow and get ready to be released into the wild.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220223000 +0000" stop="20241220230000 +0000" channel="AnimalPlanet.ee"><title lang="ee">Meet the Orangutans</title><desc lang="ee">Meet the Orangutans is a documentary series set in Borneo, in the first orangutan rehabilitation center, where the staff help these young apes prepare for life in the jungle. Join Sue Sheward and her team, as they take care of orphaned and wounded monkeys, and teach them the basic skills for survival, like tree-climbing, nest-building and finding food. Meet the friendly, fun and often even naughty orangs, as they grow and get ready to be released into the wild.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220230000 +0000" stop="20241220232300 +0000" channel="AnimalPlanet.ee"><title lang="ee">Meet the Penguins</title><desc lang="ee">Meet the Penguins is a documentary that follows the team of the Sancob Seabird Hospital in Cape Town, as they rescue penguins in need of help they encounter on the coast. These experts and volunteers give medical treatment, feed and support the incredible and vulnerable creatures, as they get ready to go back into the wild. Even when the odds are stacked the staff is dedicated to help the penguins get back on their feet. Meet the adorable characters of the penguins, each with a story of their own and a distinct personality.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220232300 +0000" stop="20241220234500 +0000" channel="AnimalPlanet.ee"><title lang="ee">Meet the Penguins</title><desc lang="ee">Meet the Penguins is a documentary that follows the team of the Sancob Seabird Hospital in Cape Town, as they rescue penguins in need of help they encounter on the coast. These experts and volunteers give medical treatment, feed and support the incredible and vulnerable creatures, as they get ready to go back into the wild. Even when the odds are stacked the staff is dedicated to help the penguins get back on their feet. Meet the adorable characters of the penguins, each with a story of their own and a distinct personality.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220234500 +0000" stop="20241221003000 +0000" channel="AnimalPlanet.ee"><title lang="ee">Alaska Monsters</title><desc lang="ee">The team heads to southern Alaska to investigate sightings of a highly temperamental Bigfoot. Todd and Rhett build a huge, electrified tepee to catch it.</desc></programme>
