<programme start="20241221011500 +0000" stop="20241221013800 +0000" channel="AnimalPlanet.ee"><title lang="ee">Meet the Orangutans</title><desc lang="ee">Meet the Orangutans is a documentary series set in Borneo, in the first orangutan rehabilitation center, where the staff help these young apes prepare for life in the jungle. Join Sue Sheward and her team, as they take care of orphaned and wounded monkeys, and teach them the basic skills for survival, like tree-climbing, nest-building and finding food. Meet the friendly, fun and often even naughty orangs, as they grow and get ready to be released into the wild.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241221013800 +0000" stop="20241221020000 +0000" channel="AnimalPlanet.ee"><title lang="ee">Meet the Orangutans</title><desc lang="ee">Meet the Orangutans is a documentary series set in Borneo, in the first orangutan rehabilitation center, where the staff help these young apes prepare for life in the jungle. Join Sue Sheward and her team, as they take care of orphaned and wounded monkeys, and teach them the basic skills for survival, like tree-climbing, nest-building and finding food. Meet the friendly, fun and often even naughty orangs, as they grow and get ready to be released into the wild.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241221020000 +0000" stop="20241221022300 +0000" channel="AnimalPlanet.ee"><title lang="ee">Meet the Penguins</title><desc lang="ee">Meet the Penguins is a documentary that follows the team of the Sancob Seabird Hospital in Cape Town, as they rescue penguins in need of help they encounter on the coast. These experts and volunteers give medical treatment, feed and support the incredible and vulnerable creatures, as they get ready to go back into the wild. Even when the odds are stacked the staff is dedicated to help the penguins get back on their feet. Meet the adorable characters of the penguins, each with a story of their own and a distinct personality.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241221022300 +0000" stop="20241221024500 +0000" channel="AnimalPlanet.ee"><title lang="ee">Meet the Penguins</title><desc lang="ee">Meet the Penguins is a documentary that follows the team of the Sancob Seabird Hospital in Cape Town, as they rescue penguins in need of help they encounter on the coast. These experts and volunteers give medical treatment, feed and support the incredible and vulnerable creatures, as they get ready to go back into the wild. Even when the odds are stacked the staff is dedicated to help the penguins get back on their feet. Meet the adorable characters of the penguins, each with a story of their own and a distinct personality.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241221024500 +0000" stop="20241221033000 +0000" channel="AnimalPlanet.ee"><title lang="ee">Animal Cops: Philadelphia</title><desc lang="ee">Documentary series that follows the people who work for The Pennsylvania Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals, based in downtown Philadelphia, and whose job is to, on a daily basis, rescue, rehabilitate and re-home unwanted or neglected animals of all types, seeking justice against the perpetrators that abused them. Although, primarily following the Law Enforcement Officers, the programme also shows the combined efforts of PSPCA Veterinarians, Technicians, Shelter Staff and Administration.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241221033000 +0000" stop="20241221041500 +0000" channel="AnimalPlanet.ee"><title lang="ee">Tanked</title><desc lang="ee">Follow aquarium enthusiasts Brett Raymer and Wayde King as they attempt to build some of the most luxurious fish tanks in the world. At Acrylic Tank Manufacturing, the brothers-in-law guide you through the design process and the building of their truly jaw-dropping aquariums. Experience the unveiling of finished tanks housed everywhere from restaurants and banks, to glamorous casinos and mansions. Join the duo in their Las Vegas workshop as they deliver some budget-shattering builds to their high-profile clientele.</desc></programme>
