<programme start="20241220230000 +0000" stop="20241221000000 +0000" channel="CNNInternational.us"><title lang="en">First Move with Julia Chatterley</title><desc lang="en">Business news show, broadcast live daily from the floor of the New York Stock Exchange. The host of the show is Julia Chatterley, a global market analyst, an anchor and correspondent for CNN. The show is fast-moving and covers the latest market moves in US and around the globe, highlights top stories in the world of business and money that never sleeps. Be the first to know the news influencing global politics, culture and finance.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241221000000 +0000" stop="20241221010000 +0000" channel="CNNInternational.us"><title lang="en">Erin Burnett OutFront</title><desc lang="en">Hosted by Erin Burnett, an expert in political science and economics, OutFront is an hour-long news programme examining the latest stories from the US and further afield. Broadcast live from either the New York studio or live on location from the site of a breaking story, the show features insightful opinions from informed guests. With expert analysis from CNN&apos;s correspondents and analysis from the show&apos;s panel, Erin Burnett OutFront dissects the stories of the day, leaving no stone unturned. Burnett, a former financial analyst for Goldman Sachs, uses her forthright approach to engage interviewees in honest discussion.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241221010000 +0000" stop="20241221020000 +0000" channel="CNNInternational.us"><title lang="en">Anderson Cooper 360</title><desc lang="en">Anderson Cooper delves into the day&apos;s news, looking beyond the broadcast to give his take, prompting us to re-think what we hear in the headlines. Cooper has covered major, international stories like the aftermath of Hurricane Katrina on the Gulf Coast, the catastrophic BP oil spill and the 2010 earthquake in Haiti, which saw the whole world fall silent. The show has won an absolute plethora of awards over the years, including GLAAD Media and Emmy awards.</desc></programme>
