<programme start="20241220170000 +0000" stop="20241220173000 +0000" channel="DiscoveryChannel.ee"><title lang="ee">How Do They Do It?</title><desc lang="ee">As the modern world becomes progressively automated and mechanised it&apos;s easy to become detached from how things are made and how they work. The hit series returns to uncover the miraculous feats of engineering which underpin life in the 21st century. How the seemingly mundane are often the result of highly sophisticated engineering and production processes. This fascinating behind-the-scenes journey delves deep into the production of everyday modern items from surfboards to satchels and trombones to cricket bats.</desc></programme>
