<programme start="20241220055000 +0000" stop="20241220063500 +0000" channel="Duo5.lv"><title lang="lv">Murder, Mystery and My Family</title><desc lang="lv">Top criminal barristers Sasha Wass and Jeremy Dein reinvestigate the historic murders of two policemen, and the mysterious case, conviction and execution of Alfred Moore. Huddersfield, 1951. Two policemen are shot dead in cold blood while staking out the farmhouse of suspected burglar Alfred Moore. Now, nearly 65 years later, Moore&apos;s daughter Bronwyne is convinced of her father&apos;s innocence and teams up with Jeremy and Sasha to investigate the case. With no murder weapon and a number of other suspects in the frame, notably a local gangster, Jeremy and Sasha have some serious concerns over the conviction. But will it be enough to clear the family name?</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220063500 +0000" stop="20241220071500 +0000" channel="Duo5.lv"><title lang="lv">Casey Anthony: Killer Mom?</title><desc lang="lv">A 3-part documentary crime series examines one of the most famous cases in the USA- the Casey Anthony case, the 22-year-old Florida woman who was accused of the murder of her 2-year-old daughter, Caylee. The viewers will have a chance to meet Caylee&apos;s grandparents, Cindy and George Anthony and hear their first-hand story of the tragic details surrounding the death of their granddaughter. The series will also reveal some new details surrounding the problematic investigation of the case that outraged the nation.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220071500 +0000" stop="20241220080000 +0000" channel="Duo5.lv"><title lang="lv">Disappeared</title><desc lang="lv">Disappeared is an American documentary TV show that contains dramatic re-enactments and interviews with law enforcement officers, investigators, and relatives connected with cases in which individuals have gone missing without a trace. The stories are heartbreaking and unbelievable, the families of people who have gone missing never give up hope. Some cases have tragic endings, some are heartwarming, but most of them are still open which makes the agony of the families go on.</desc></programme>
