<programme start="20241220095000 +0000" stop="20241220100500 +0000" channel="Duo6.lt"><title lang="lt">Two and a Half Men</title><desc lang="lt">After being tricked into helping Alan and Judith produce Jake&apos;s class musical, Charlie is flattered to find out that the kids know all the words to his jingles. Alan is blindsided with divorce papers from Judith, causing strife which results in Charlie, who refuses to deal with the pre-pubers without a snootful, having to produce the play on his own. Jake is crushed when he realizes that a reconciliation between his parents might never happen.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220100500 +0000" stop="20241220103000 +0000" channel="Duo6.lt"><title lang="lt">Two and a Half Men</title><desc lang="lt">After his divorce, Alan Harper, a struggling chiropractor, moves in with his brother Charlie Harper, a womanizer and successful jingle writer as Charlie &quot;temporarily&quot; allows him and his son Jake, a food-obsessed, lazy kid to join him in his luxurious beach-house complicating Charlie&apos;s carefree life. Compulsively neat and control-freak Alan, hedonistic free spirited bachelor Charlie, Jake and other peculiar characters - Evelyn, their vain mother, Charlie&apos;s outspoken cleaning lady Berta and his rich, self-confessed stalker neighbor Rose soon get themselves into an abundance of crazy and hilarious situations.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220103000 +0000" stop="20241220105000 +0000" channel="Duo6.lt"><title lang="lt">The Nanny</title><desc lang="lt">Fran Fine, a fashionista and make-up saleswoman, shows up on the doorstep of the Sheffield family and becomes the nanny to Maggie, Brighton, and Grace, the children of British Broadway producer Maxwell Sheffield. The householf is managed by the acerbic butler Niles, who supports Fran, and often visited by Maxwell&apos;s business partner C.C. Babcock, who is determined to undermine her, as she sees Maxwell&apos;s attraction to Fran but is interested in him herself.</desc></programme>
