<programme start="20241220082000 +0000" stop="20241220090500 +0000" channel="EpicDrama.ee"><title lang="ee">Murdoch Mysteries</title><desc lang="ee">Murdoch Mysteries is a fine example of canadian detective series. The main character is William Murdoch, a talented police detective working in Toronto, Ontario in the late 19th century. He uses methods of forensic science to solve the mysterious murder cases and these methods are ahead of his time. His motto is &quot;Nothing is impossible&quot; and his confidence and determination help him to cope with the most complicated tasks that are beyond the scope of other detectives. William is not alone in his investigations, his superior, inspector Brackenreid, Doctor Julia Ogden, expert skilled in pathology and the inexperienced but enthusiastic assistant Constable George Crabtree are by his side. Sometimes real historical figures appear in the series, such as Jack London, William Churchill, Nikola Tesla etc.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220090500 +0000" stop="20241220095000 +0000" channel="EpicDrama.ee"><title lang="ee">All Creatures Great and Small</title><desc lang="ee">It&apos;s spring in 1938, and James&apos;s parents are overjoyed when he&apos;s offered a position at his old mentor&apos;s forward-thinking practice in Glasgow. When he returns to the Dales, James is reminded of how much he loves the place and the people - and thinks of one person who it would be worth staying in the Dales for. Since Helen Alderson left Hugh Hulton at the altar, she has kept a low profile and James has given her the space she needed. But the pair find themselves forced together again when neighbouring farmer Rob Benson&apos;s sheep are in trouble. Inspired by his time at the Glasgow surgery, James pushes Siegfried to let Tristan do more veterinary jobs so that they can take on more small animal cases at Skeldale House. Tristan tends to a budgerigar whilst Mrs Hall uncovers a difficult truth.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220095000 +0000" stop="20241220104000 +0000" channel="EpicDrama.ee"><title lang="ee">All Creatures Great and Small</title><desc lang="ee">British drama series set in the 1930s, centering on the eccentric veterinarian Siegfried Farnon and his colleagues, James Herriot, and Tristan, Siegried&apos;s younger brother. Working out of the stunning Skeldale House in the Yorkshire Dales , the trio of companions endeavour themselves to the surrounding community by providing a valuable service to the region&apos;s animals. Adapted from If Only They Could Talk by James Herriot (Alf Wight&apos;s pen name), the delightful series is a celebration of the wonderful stories penned by Wight, bringing to life the iconic characters from his much-loved books.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220104000 +0000" stop="20241220121500 +0000" channel="EpicDrama.ee"><title lang="ee">Agatha Christie&apos;s Marple</title><desc lang="ee">The sleuth is called to Gossington Hall by her old friend Dolly Bantry (Joanna Lumley) when she finds the corpse of an unknown blonde in the library of her home. It soon transpires that there is no shortage of suspects, including local bad boy Basil Blake (Ben Miller) and Dolly&apos;s husband Arthur (James Fox), but when the victim is identified as a dancer in line to inherit a fortune, enquiries take a different turn. Crime drama, starring Geraldine McEwan, with Simon Callow, Jack Davenport and Tara Fitzgerald.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220121500 +0000" stop="20241220130000 +0000" channel="EpicDrama.ee"><title lang="ee">Grantchester</title><desc lang="ee">Drama series adapted from the novels by James Runcie about a village in Cambridgeshire where Sidney Chambers is the local vicar. When Guy and Amanda ask Sidney to perform their wedding ceremony, the heartbroken vicar takes solace in a bottle. In spite of his disappointment, Sidney helps Isabel Livingstone to prepare for her wedding to Arthur Evans despite her mother&apos;s wishes. However, when her mother Daisy is found dead, Sidney finds himself being dragged into the investigation reluctantly.</desc></programme>
