<programme start="20241220160000 +0000" stop="20241220180000 +0000" channel="FilmZone.lv"><title lang="lv">Due Date</title><desc lang="lv">In this comedy about fatherhood, Robert Downey Jr. (Iron Man, Sherlock Holmes) plays Peter Highman, an expectant first-time father whose wife&apos;s due date is a mere five days away. As Peter hurries to catch a flight home from Atlanta to be at her side for the birth, his best intentions go completely awry when a chance encounter with aspiring actor Ethan Tremblay (The Hangover&apos;s Zach Galifianakis) forces Peter to hitch a ride with the slacker - on what turns out to be a cross-country road trip that will ultimately destroy several cars, numerous friendships and Peter&apos;s last nerve. Oscar® winners Jamie Foxx (Ray) and Alan Arkin (Little Miss Sunshine) add to the chaotic fun as Downey&apos;s friend and father, respectively. Produced and directed by comedy powerhouse Todd Phillips (in his follow-up to the $400+ million worldwide box-office smash The Hangover), this road trip comedy represents the ultimate buddy comedy...without the buddies!</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220180000 +0000" stop="20241220201500 +0000" channel="FilmZone.lv"><title lang="lv">Queenpins</title><desc lang="lv">Kristen Bell and Kirby Howell-Baptiste star as two women who amassed millions through coupon fraud in this comedy crime caper inspired by real events. Unhappily married Connie (Bell) and Rick (Joel McHale) have amassed huge debt in their attempts to have a child. But there&apos;s one thing that gets Connie going: a &apos;coupon high&apos;. She can slash a shopping bill to virtually nothing using those magic little chits. It&apos;s like free money. Hang on, it&apos;s like free money... With this revelation in mind, Connie joins forces with her neighbour JoJo (Howell-Baptiste, who&apos;s living with her mum after identity fraud left her with a horrendous credit rating. They discover that there&apos;s a company in Mexico that produces coupons, and enlist a low-wage employee to print fake ones. It&apos;s a victimless crime... or at least the victims are huge conglomerates that&apos;ll just write off the scam. But Connie and JoJo didn&apos;t figure on pernickety loss prevention officer Ken (Paul Walter Hauser), who&apos;s not having it; a crime is a crime after all. And things really spice up when US Postal Service investigator Simon (Vince Vaughn) joins the hunt. Simon doesn&apos;t carry the mail, he carries a gun. But can they track down the cunning pair? Well, they could start with JoJo&apos;s YouTube vlog. Doh! Written and directed by Aron Gaudet and Gita Pullapilly. Network Premiere.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220201500 +0000" stop="20241220230000 +0000" channel="FilmZone.lv"><title lang="lv">Shutter Island</title><desc lang="lv">Leonardo DiCaprio and Mark Ruffalo star in Martin Scorsese&apos;s dark, 1950s-set mystery thriller, based on Dennis Lehane&apos;s bestseller. Teddy Daniels (DiCaprio) was among the US troops who liberated the Dachau concentration camp from the Nazis during World War II. The horrors he witnessed there, together with other grim memories from the war and his wife&apos;s death, haunt him. Now, Daniels is a US Marshal, and he and his partner (Ruffalo) have been sent to investigate the mysterious disappearance of a woman who murdered her three children. She has, somehow, vanished from the ultra-secure asylum for the criminally insane on Shutter Island, located far out to sea on a forbidding rocky outcrop. As a massive storm rolls in, threatening to keep them on the island for days, the detectives&apos; disquiet at the asylum&apos;s relaxed regime starts to morph into fear, as they begin to suspect that terrible things take place within its walls... Also starring Ben Kingsley and Max von Sydow.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220230000 +0000" stop="20241221005500 +0000" channel="FilmZone.lv"><title lang="lv">Due Date</title><desc lang="lv">In this comedy about fatherhood, Robert Downey Jr. (Iron Man, Sherlock Holmes) plays Peter Highman, an expectant first-time father whose wife&apos;s due date is a mere five days away. As Peter hurries to catch a flight home from Atlanta to be at her side for the birth, his best intentions go completely awry when a chance encounter with aspiring actor Ethan Tremblay (The Hangover&apos;s Zach Galifianakis) forces Peter to hitch a ride with the slacker - on what turns out to be a cross-country road trip that will ultimately destroy several cars, numerous friendships and Peter&apos;s last nerve. Oscar® winners Jamie Foxx (Ray) and Alan Arkin (Little Miss Sunshine) add to the chaotic fun as Downey&apos;s friend and father, respectively. Produced and directed by comedy powerhouse Todd Phillips (in his follow-up to the $400+ million worldwide box-office smash The Hangover), this road trip comedy represents the ultimate buddy comedy...without the buddies!</desc></programme>
