<programme start="20241221023500 +0000" stop="20241221030000 +0000" channel="FX.lt"><title lang="lt">M.O.D.O.K.</title><desc lang="lt">Jodie&apos;s celebrity is on the rise and M.O.D.O.K. plans on winning her back from her new boyfriend, the superhero Wonder Man. Jodie and her publicist invite M.O.D.O.K. to a party, knowing his temper will bring publicity. M.O.D.O.K. provokes Wonder Man into attacking him at the party and is kicked out. Wonder Man leaves Jodie when he sees she&apos;s only using him for exposure. Melissa and Lou bond over their disappointment in their parents. M.O.D.O.K. and Jodie have sex when he goes to apologize, and it is revealed who exactly was behind her publicist&apos;s actions.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241221030000 +0000" stop="20241221032500 +0000" channel="FX.lt"><title lang="lt">M.O.D.O.K.</title><desc lang="lt">M.O.D.O.K. suddenly starts acting like a model employee, dutifully delivering mail and making tablets. Austin has a change of heart and tries to inform M.O.D.O.K. who really is running GRUMBL. Thrown by M.O.D.O.K.&apos;s new behavior, Gary thinks it&apos;s Austin&apos;s fault, and Monica suspects M.O.D.O.K. is planning something against her. Eventually, M.O.D.O.K. reveals that he is selling his shares in AIM to Tony Stark and starts a new business with Monica. Austin misses the chance to tell M.O.D.O.K. the truth about GRUMBL.</desc></programme>
