<programme start="20241220152500 +0000" stop="20241220155000 +0000" channel="KidZoneMax.lv"><title lang="lv">Bunk&apos;d</title><desc lang="lv">Bunk&apos;d shows Ravi Ross and his sisters Emma and Zuri who decide to leave noisy streets of New York and set off to a rustic summer camp Kikiwaka in Maine where their parents met as teenagers. The camp got its name after a magic creature Kikiwaka that leaves nearby. From the first minutes of their stay guys realize that holidays are not going to be easy and relaxing, as the head of Kikiwaka turns out to remember their Mom who stole her boyfriend. That boyfriend later became the father of the three. Plus the conditions in the camp are very specific and far from perfect, health code and safety regulations are seriously violated. Ravi has a weird roommate, Zuri&apos;s roommate is a nerd, so kids start to doubt whether it is worth staying. Also modern technologies like phones and notebooks are not available in the camp, which makes it even harder. Fortunately the teens are smart enough to figure out their way out of the most difficult and strange situations.</desc></programme>
