<programme start="20241220193000 +0000" stop="20241220201500 +0000" channel="NationalGeographic.ee"><title lang="ee">Life Below Zero: Port Protection Alaska</title><desc lang="ee">Sam sends Troy underwater in search of sunken shipwreck treasure. Mary dodges wolves on the opening day of deer season to take a shot at a big prize. Curly sets sail to land halibut for winter. Oliver goes on a risky solo mission for firewood.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220201500 +0000" stop="20241220210000 +0000" channel="NationalGeographic.ee"><title lang="ee">Life Below Zero: Port Protection Alaska</title><desc lang="ee">With fall in full effect, residents race to complete projects before winter. Curly constructs a hunting blind on opening day of duck season. Oliver and Breanna try to load up on fresh crab and shellfish. Troy dives into freezing water to recover lost gear. And Sam and Squibb work together to build a desperately needed firefighting tool.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220210000 +0000" stop="20241220214500 +0000" channel="NationalGeographic.ee"><title lang="ee">Life Below Zero: Port Protection Alaska</title><desc lang="ee">With winter quickly approaching, the residents of Port Protection begin the long task of stocking their pantries. Curly takes Junior out for the first duck hunt of the season and encounters a pack of apex predators. Matt helps his father restock his junk pile with treasures. Breanna shows Veronica the bounty of the land. And Carl kills two &quot;birds&quot; with one chainsaw.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220214500 +0000" stop="20241220222500 +0000" channel="NationalGeographic.ee"><title lang="ee">Trafficked with Mariana van Zeller</title><desc lang="ee">An alarming message from her son&apos;s middle school about MDMA sparks Mariana to investigate. She follows the supply chain of &quot;the love drug&quot; from the clubs of LA back to its booming epicenter in the Netherlands, where a mob-infested underworld has recently murdered a well-known journalist. Is it possible that MDMA consumption in the U.S. is helping to turn the Netherlands into a narco-state?</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220222500 +0000" stop="20241220231000 +0000" channel="NationalGeographic.ee"><title lang="ee">Trafficked with Mariana van Zeller</title><desc lang="ee">Mariana embarks on a 3,000-mile journey from Africa to the Middle East to uncover the ways in which black market oil is fueling terrorist groups around the globe. Her investigation discovers how this &quot;black gold&quot; is stolen, smuggled and finding its way into the hands of America&apos;s most dangerous enemies.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220231000 +0000" stop="20241220235500 +0000" channel="NationalGeographic.ee"><title lang="ee">Air Crash Investigation</title><desc lang="ee">Taking off during a major storm, a brand-new 737 falls from the sky over West Africa, and an international group of investigators soon descends on Cameroon. Submerged in mud and water, Kenya Airlines Flight 507 crashed into a mangrove swamp, killing everyone on board. And while investigators ultimately pinpoint one fatal mistake that triggered the tragedy, they also uncover a lethal cascade of issues that sent the passenger jet spiralling toward the ground.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220235500 +0000" stop="20241221004500 +0000" channel="NationalGeographic.ee"><title lang="ee">Air Crash Investigation</title><desc lang="ee">Air France Flight #296 (Airbus A320) June 26th, 1988 The Airbus A-320 the worlds most sophisticated passenger jet takes off for its maiden passenger flight and first-ever public demonstration. The plane is headed for the Habsheim Air Show where the pilots are planning a breathtaking, low-altitude fly-over. But after getting into position over the tiny airfield the exhibition turns to disaster. The plane plows into a forest and is consumed by flames. It is a horrible tragedy, and a public relations nightmare for Airbus. With such a huge investment on the line, there is enormous pressure on investigators to determine whether the pilot or the plane was at fault.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241221004500 +0000" stop="20241221013000 +0000" channel="NationalGeographic.ee"><title lang="ee">Air Crash Investigation</title><desc lang="ee">Every time a plane crashes, the world takes notice. And so do the experts whose job it is to figure out what happened. Air Crash Investigation uncovers the truth behind the most legendary aviation disasters, and every episode features eyewitness accounts, captivating reenactments, state-of-the-art CGI, and interviews with the investigators who ultimately determined what went wrong. This season on Air Crash Investigation: Conflicting stories emerge after a Swedish cargo plane spirals to the ground; an African airliner crashes in the wilderness and the cause proves too sinister to be believed; and, when a Pakistani passenger jet disappears on approach to Kathmandu, Nepalese investigators must determine how it ended up on a crash course with the Himalayas.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241221013000 +0000" stop="20241221021500 +0000" channel="NationalGeographic.ee"><title lang="ee">Air Crash Investigation</title><desc lang="ee">Every time a plane crashes, the world takes notice. And so do the experts whose job it is to figure out what happened. Air Crash Investigation uncovers the truth behind the most legendary aviation disasters, and every episode features eyewitness accounts, captivating reenactments, state-of-the-art CGI, and interviews with the investigators who ultimately determined what went wrong. This season on Air Crash Investigation: Conflicting stories emerge after a Swedish cargo plane spirals to the ground; an African airliner crashes in the wilderness and the cause proves too sinister to be believed; and, when a Pakistani passenger jet disappears on approach to Kathmandu, Nepalese investigators must determine how it ended up on a crash course with the Himalayas.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241221021500 +0000" stop="20241221023500 +0000" channel="NationalGeographic.ee"><title lang="ee">Science of Stupid</title><desc lang="ee">Science of Stupid, series 8. Dallas Campbell hosts the show that combines serious science with some of the craziest, most spectacular user generated clips ever recorded. In each programme we show 40 to 50 clips of misadventure: ordinary folk making extraordinary mistakes and paying the price. We analyse the science behind the mishaps, with the help of bespoke animation and super slow-motion cinematography.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241221023500 +0000" stop="20241221030000 +0000" channel="NationalGeographic.ee"><title lang="ee">Science of Stupid</title><desc lang="ee">Science of Stupid, series 8. Dallas Campbell hosts the show that combines serious science with some of the craziest, most spectacular user generated clips ever recorded. In each programme we show 40 to 50 clips of misadventure: ordinary folk making extraordinary mistakes and paying the price. We analyse the science behind the mishaps, with the help of bespoke animation and super slow-motion cinematography.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241221030000 +0000" stop="20241221044500 +0000" channel="NationalGeographic.ee"><title lang="ee">Sugarcane</title><desc lang="ee">A discovery of unmarked graves at an Indian residential school run by the Catholic Church in Canada sparks a national outcry. In response, an Indigenous community opens their own investigation into atrocities at a nearby school, revealing a system designed to destroy their way of life. Survivors excavate their own truths, finding the courage to face the past and break cycles of trauma.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241221044500 +0000" stop="20241221062500 +0000" channel="NationalGeographic.ee"><title lang="ee">The Mission</title><desc lang="ee">American Christian missionary John Chau was killed when he tried to contact and convert some of the worlds last uncontacted indigenous peoples The Sentinelese. Contradictory and divided reactions from the public and even within his own family reveal a deeper understanding of the real John Chau a young man with an adventurous spirit and a singular obsession. Through exclusive interviews, archival footage of Johns journey to North Sentinel and his detailed diaries, this film explores the antiquated notions of exploration that shaped him, the evangelical community that drove his quest, his own fathers heartbreak, and the lasting repercussions of this complex story.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220045000 +0000" stop="20241220051500 +0000" channel="NationalGeographic.lv"><title lang="lv">Food Factory USA</title><desc lang="lv">On this episode of Food Factory USA: It takes mountains of meat, onions, and hamburger buns to keep up with the hot demand for White Castle&apos;s iconic sliders; this awesome machine processes and prepares 1.7 million mandarin oranges every hour; and these heart-shaped crackers are showered with love - and sesame seeds.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220051500 +0000" stop="20241220053500 +0000" channel="NationalGeographic.lv"><title lang="lv">Food Factory USA</title><desc lang="lv">On this episode of Food Factory USA: Get the inside scoop on the iconic, cult-favorite PEZ candies and their trusty dispenser sidekicks; discover the secret to making the cheez-y-est bags of crispy mini waffles; and there&apos;s plenty of &quot;amore&quot; in this frozen chicken Parmesan with spaghetti meal from Texas.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220053500 +0000" stop="20241220062000 +0000" channel="NationalGeographic.lv"><title lang="lv">Drain the Oceans</title><desc lang="lv">DRAIN THE OCEAN pulls the plug on the ocean to reveal hidden secrets and lost worlds, using ground-breaking technology, breath-taking photography and insight from top marine archaeologists. The series delivers penetrating new insights into the epic history of human civilisation and the deep history of Planet Earth itself, exposing sunken cities, shipwrecks and the amazing natural wonders of the deep.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220062000 +0000" stop="20241220070500 +0000" channel="NationalGeographic.lv"><title lang="lv">Drain the Oceans</title><desc lang="lv">War...Weather...and human error have led to some of the worst maritime disasters in US history. But imagine if we could empty the oceans, letting the water drain away to reveal these secrets of Americas sea floor. Pearl Harbor, who fired the first shot? What are the dangerous forces that make Alcatraz and the San Francisco Bay so deadly? And how did drilling for oil result in one of the biggest environmental disasters in US history? Drained dry we reveal these sunken mysteries along Americas shores.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220070500 +0000" stop="20241220075000 +0000" channel="NationalGeographic.lv"><title lang="lv">Ice Road Rescue</title><desc lang="lv">&quot;Ice Road Rescue&quot; portrays a group of heroic tow truck rescue workers. When winter hits Norway the transport roads turn into treacherous bobsleigh tracks. Every day the rescuers fight to keep this routes open by rescuing heavy trailers stuck in the mountain terrain. Winter storms, avalanches and lack of daylight through the winter season are just some of the challenges they have to face, working close to the polar circle. Extreme winter conditions that often make them risk their lives. &quot;Ice Road Rescue&quot; shows the ultimate man versus nature.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220075000 +0000" stop="20241220083500 +0000" channel="NationalGeographic.lv"><title lang="lv">Ice Road Rescue</title><desc lang="lv">Thord has his hands full with keeping the road open while the snow keeps falling. Although it&apos;s a neverending job, Thord is well aware of the importance of these weather conditions as a necessity for his business. Jo Roger in the north get a lot of work from the trucks driving in the forrest, filled with timber. Bjørn is on the mountain rescuing a truck when a car tries to bypass him, gets stuck, and then has to be saved by Bjørn</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220083500 +0000" stop="20241220092000 +0000" channel="NationalGeographic.lv"><title lang="lv">Ice Road Rescue</title><desc lang="lv">In &quot;Ice Road Rescue&quot; we follow a group of heroic and tough men who challenges the rought winter conditions in Norway by rescuing heavy trailers passing through the norwegian mountain terrain. We follow our main charachters, the heroic rescue workers, in both the southern and norhern mountains of norway. With extreme tought winter conditions that often results in in dangerous rescues, our men always come to the rescue. This is man vs nature and no rescue is too small for our rescue workers.</desc></programme>
