<programme start="20241221023500 +0000" stop="20241221030000 +0000" channel="NationalGeographicWild.ee"><title lang="ee">America&apos;s Wild Spaces</title><desc lang="ee">This show explores the unbridled natural beauty of America&apos;s national parks and highlights some of the most awe-inspiring scenery on the planet. Travelling beyond the more conventional tourist hot-spots, the viewer is transported to the hidden wonders of America&apos;s wild spaces. Episodes include joining a scientific exploration of the 277 mile long Grand Canyon, studying its geological history, exploring the microscopic colonies of vegetation and examining its unique creatures; journeying through the Everglades, a 1.5 million acre home to strange creatures, carnivorous plants, amphibious birds and fish that can breathe air; and navigating across the northwest archipelago of Hawaii following a team of diving scientists as they inspect the unique aquaeous flora and fauna.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241221030000 +0000" stop="20241221034500 +0000" channel="NationalGeographicWild.ee"><title lang="ee">Lions: The Hunt For Survival</title><desc lang="ee">Three lionesses from three very different hunting arenas. Each face their own challenges, but all gun for one clear goal - to kill.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241221034500 +0000" stop="20241221041000 +0000" channel="NationalGeographicWild.ee"><title lang="ee">America&apos;s Wild Spaces</title><desc lang="ee">This show explores the unbridled natural beauty of America&apos;s national parks and highlights some of the most awe-inspiring scenery on the planet. Travelling beyond the more conventional tourist hot-spots, the viewer is transported to the hidden wonders of America&apos;s wild spaces. Episodes include joining a scientific exploration of the 277 mile long Grand Canyon, studying its geological history, exploring the microscopic colonies of vegetation and examining its unique creatures; journeying through the Everglades, a 1.5 million acre home to strange creatures, carnivorous plants, amphibious birds and fish that can breathe air; and navigating across the northwest archipelago of Hawaii following a team of diving scientists as they inspect the unique aquaeous flora and fauna.</desc></programme>
