<programme start="20241221010000 +0000" stop="20241221015000 +0000" channel="NationalGeographicWild.lv"><title lang="lv">Africa&apos;s Deadliest</title><desc lang="lv">A national Geographic documentary looking into the deadliest animals that roam Africa. Examining animals that have evolved complex weapons from teeth to claws and agility so that they can protect themselves and battle effectively. From elephant tusks that can defend or attack to the fur, speed and agility of seals. Showing how these animals have exceptional skills and power alongside their body features that have developed into ideal tools for their needs.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241221015000 +0000" stop="20241221023500 +0000" channel="NationalGeographicWild.lv"><title lang="lv">Africa&apos;s Deadliest</title><desc lang="lv">A national Geographic documentary looking into the deadliest animals that roam Africa. Examining animals that have evolved complex weapons from teeth to claws and agility so that they can protect themselves and battle effectively. From elephant tusks that can defend or attack to the fur, speed and agility of seals. Showing how these animals have exceptional skills and power alongside their body features that have developed into ideal tools for their needs.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241221023500 +0000" stop="20241221030000 +0000" channel="NationalGeographicWild.lv"><title lang="lv">America&apos;s Wild Spaces</title><desc lang="lv">This show explores the unbridled natural beauty of America&apos;s national parks and highlights some of the most awe-inspiring scenery on the planet. Travelling beyond the more conventional tourist hot-spots, the viewer is transported to the hidden wonders of America&apos;s wild spaces. Episodes include joining a scientific exploration of the 277 mile long Grand Canyon, studying its geological history, exploring the microscopic colonies of vegetation and examining its unique creatures; journeying through the Everglades, a 1.5 million acre home to strange creatures, carnivorous plants, amphibious birds and fish that can breathe air; and navigating across the northwest archipelago of Hawaii following a team of diving scientists as they inspect the unique aquaeous flora and fauna.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241221030000 +0000" stop="20241221034500 +0000" channel="NationalGeographicWild.lv"><title lang="lv">Lions: The Hunt For Survival</title><desc lang="lv">Three lionesses from three very different hunting arenas. Each face their own challenges, but all gun for one clear goal - to kill.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241221034500 +0000" stop="20241221041000 +0000" channel="NationalGeographicWild.lv"><title lang="lv">America&apos;s Wild Spaces</title><desc lang="lv">This show explores the unbridled natural beauty of America&apos;s national parks and highlights some of the most awe-inspiring scenery on the planet. Travelling beyond the more conventional tourist hot-spots, the viewer is transported to the hidden wonders of America&apos;s wild spaces. Episodes include joining a scientific exploration of the 277 mile long Grand Canyon, studying its geological history, exploring the microscopic colonies of vegetation and examining its unique creatures; journeying through the Everglades, a 1.5 million acre home to strange creatures, carnivorous plants, amphibious birds and fish that can breathe air; and navigating across the northwest archipelago of Hawaii following a team of diving scientists as they inspect the unique aquaeous flora and fauna.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241221041000 +0000" stop="20241221043000 +0000" channel="NationalGeographicWild.lv"><title lang="lv">America&apos;s Wild Spaces</title><desc lang="lv">This show explores the unbridled natural beauty of America&apos;s national parks and highlights some of the most awe-inspiring scenery on the planet. Travelling beyond the more conventional tourist hot-spots, the viewer is transported to the hidden wonders of America&apos;s wild spaces. Episodes include joining a scientific exploration of the 277 mile long Grand Canyon, studying its geological history, exploring the microscopic colonies of vegetation and examining its unique creatures; journeying through the Everglades, a 1.5 million acre home to strange creatures, carnivorous plants, amphibious birds and fish that can breathe air; and navigating across the northwest archipelago of Hawaii following a team of diving scientists as they inspect the unique aquaeous flora and fauna.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241221043000 +0000" stop="20241221051500 +0000" channel="NationalGeographicWild.lv"><title lang="lv">Africa&apos;s Deadly Kingdom</title><desc lang="lv">Instead of providing in-depth examinations of the fauna of the continent of Africa, this nature series alternatively focuses on the hostile and unforgiving landscapes that the animals have to survive in. Africa is home to some of the most extreme and diverse environments on the planet, from arid deserts to lush rainforests, mountainous peaks to mighty river and lake systems, savannah grasslands to rugged coastline. This show explores these different regions and documents how the plants and creatures that inhabit them endure places where there are few resources of food and water or where competition is rife and life-threatening. The unique demands placed on these plants and animals have resulted in the development of incredibly resilient species that remain successful against all the odds.</desc></programme>
