<programme start="20241220080000 +0000" stop="20241220090000 +0000" channel="SetantaSports2.lv"><title lang="lv">Football: Bundesliga</title><desc lang="lv">Germany has the most attended football league in the world, in the Bundesliga. We bring these authentic fab experiences to your living room with all the key moments of the 2019-20 season, to ensure that your appetite for German football is well and truly met. The likes of Borussia Dortmund and Bayern Munich are met with stern competition this season, as RB Leipzig look to build on their third-placed finish from last season. This programme brings all the games of the german top-flight into one place, so that you can easily catch up with the week&apos;s action. As we reach the business end-of-the-season, watch the victors and losers dictate the final table. With relegation spots and Champions League places yet to be decided, it promises to be a rather exciting conclusion for all those concerned.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220090000 +0000" stop="20241220110000 +0000" channel="SetantaSports2.lv"><title lang="lv">Football: LaLiga</title><desc lang="lv">La Liga (The Campeonato Nacional de Liga de Primera División) is the men&apos;s top professional football division of the Spanish football league system. It is administered by the National Professional Football League and has 20 contestants, with the three lowest-placed teams at the end of each season relegated to the Segunda División and replaced by the top two teams and a play-off winner in that division. Nine teams have become champions, Real Madrid has got the title 33 times and FC Barcelona 26 times. La Liga is one of the most popular professional sports leagues in the world and the top league in Europe over the last five years.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220110000 +0000" stop="20241220130000 +0000" channel="SetantaSports2.lv"><title lang="lv">Football: Bundesliga</title><desc lang="lv">Germany has the most attended football league in the world, in the Bundesliga. We bring these authentic fab experiences to your living room with all the key moments of the 2019-20 season, to ensure that your appetite for German football is well and truly met. The likes of Borussia Dortmund and Bayern Munich are met with stern competition this season, as RB Leipzig look to build on their third-placed finish from last season. This programme brings all the games of the german top-flight into one place, so that you can easily catch up with the week&apos;s action. As we reach the business end-of-the-season, watch the victors and losers dictate the final table. With relegation spots and Champions League places yet to be decided, it promises to be a rather exciting conclusion for all those concerned.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220130000 +0000" stop="20241220150000 +0000" channel="SetantaSports2.lv"><title lang="lv">Football: French Ligue 1</title><desc lang="lv">PSG, AS Monaco, Marseille, Olympique Lyonnais &amp; Lille... just to name a few. Ligue 1 is currently full of well-organised football teams and incredible European talent, who are a complement to the sport. As the highest professional division in France, it has established itself as one of the top five leagues on the continent. Lyon are the most successful team in regards to consecutive titles, whereas PSG and AS Monaco have managed to propel themselves to the highest achievements in the league, with calculated foreign investment. With the latter coming from a principality, Ligue 1 is another example of a domestic league that provides cross-border competition. From southern wine-growing regions such as Bordeaux, to the historically renowned capital of Paris, we cover the whole of France.</desc></programme>
