<programme start="20241220043500 +0000" stop="20241220050500 +0000" channel="ViasatHistory.ee"><title lang="ee">Cursed Bloodlines</title><desc lang="ee">Documentary series that examines various family curses - the Kennedy Curse, the Grimaldi Curse, the Pharaoh Curse, the Getty Curse, the Mad Monk Curse,... and tells the true stories about famous families and their tragedies. These powerful families seemingly had it all, yet years of bad luck suggest that not even money or power could protect dynasties that are mentioned in this series. The documentary will try to answer if the source of their misfortune could be pride, wealth, genetics or something much more sinister.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220050500 +0000" stop="20241220060500 +0000" channel="ViasatHistory.ee"><title lang="ee">History Uncovered</title><desc lang="ee">Documentary series that revisits some of the biggest history-related myths of the 20th century, in order to shed a new light and uncover the real truth behind some of them. You will have a chance to reveal some details that have been forgotten or sometimes overshadowed. We believe that Hiroshima caused Japan to surrender, that the Marshall Plan saved Europe, that Adolf Hitler was a military genius, and that Mao Zedong was a necessary evil for China&apos;s modernization. Although this is partly correct, this series will provide an answer to a question - What if the truth was slightly different?</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220060500 +0000" stop="20241220071000 +0000" channel="ViasatHistory.ee"><title lang="ee">Treasures with Bettany Hughes</title><desc lang="ee">With unprecedented access to unfolding excavations and some of the best finds of recent years, Professor Bettany Hughes explores ancient archaeological sites that shed light on the modern human story of civilisation; championing what ordinary people, through time, can achieve through sheer force of will and inspiration. These are neglected stories from unheard voices in extraordinary, often overlooked places. In this episode, Bettany explores mountainous Albania, the hidden gem of the Balkans once known as the mystical land of Illyria. She journeys to epic fortress towns and breathtaking archaeological sites and encounters a richly diverse history and culture. Bettany visits the ancient city of Butrint, meets remote communities in the spectacular Albanian Alps, discovers the Ottoman town of Gjirokaste?r and goes underground to the secret bunker of former communist dictator Enver Hoxha.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220071000 +0000" stop="20241220081500 +0000" channel="ViasatHistory.ee"><title lang="ee">Eiffel: Towers&apos; War</title><desc lang="ee">Behind the emblematic Eiffel Tower lies the story of a French challenge launched at the end of the 19th century: to build a tower a thousand feet high. The project was part of the period&apos;s radical transformation: iron versus stone, engineering versus architecture. We rediscover this race to the heights.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220081500 +0000" stop="20241220092500 +0000" channel="ViasatHistory.ee"><title lang="ee">Vatican - The Timeless City of Popes</title><desc lang="ee">Viasat History. Guided by historians deciphering the Vatican&apos;s rich archives following recent restorations and excavations, the Vatican delivers new untold secrets and reveals a fascinating historical saga.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220092500 +0000" stop="20241220103000 +0000" channel="ViasatHistory.ee"><title lang="ee">The Rise of the Dictators</title><desc lang="ee">Dictators might seem all-powerful, but their position in reality depends on a network of individuals who benefit from the dictator being in power - and their support doesn&apos;t come cheap.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220103000 +0000" stop="20241220113000 +0000" channel="ViasatHistory.ee"><title lang="ee">World War II: The Price of Empire</title><desc lang="ee">Documentary series that tells the story of the greatest man made event in history - World War II, from the beginning to an end, using archive footage and testimonies of more than fifty eyewitnesses to the war. Often the story of WWII begins with the rise of the Third Reich in Germany, and is told from 1 September 1939 with Germany&apos;s invasion of Poland. But this story will start earlier, as empires of the east had been in conflict since Japan&apos;s invasion of China in 1937. The wars of east and west fused to become the Second World War, changing the political map of the world.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220113000 +0000" stop="20241220123000 +0000" channel="ViasatHistory.ee"><title lang="ee">D-Day: The 80th Anniversary</title><desc lang="ee">This documentary shows a different side of D-Day: not just the famous shots of the beaches at Normandy, but the troops, sailors and civilians on the South Coast of England preparing for battle too.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220123000 +0000" stop="20241220133500 +0000" channel="ViasatHistory.ee"><title lang="ee">History Uncovered</title><desc lang="ee">Documentary series that revisits some of the biggest history-related myths of the 20th century, in order to shed a new light and uncover the real truth behind some of them. You will have a chance to reveal some details that have been forgotten or sometimes overshadowed. We believe that Hiroshima caused Japan to surrender, that the Marshall Plan saved Europe, that Adolf Hitler was a military genius, and that Mao Zedong was a necessary evil for China&apos;s modernization. Although this is partly correct, this series will provide an answer to a question - What if the truth was slightly different?</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220133500 +0000" stop="20241220145000 +0000" channel="ViasatHistory.ee"><title lang="ee">Eiffel: Towers&apos; War</title><desc lang="ee">Behind the emblematic Eiffel Tower lies the story of a French challenge launched at the end of the 19th century: to build a tower a thousand feet high. The project was part of the period&apos;s radical transformation: iron versus stone, engineering versus architecture. We rediscover this race to the heights.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220145000 +0000" stop="20241220155000 +0000" channel="ViasatHistory.ee"><title lang="ee">Treasures with Bettany Hughes</title><desc lang="ee">With unprecedented access to unfolding excavations and some of the best finds of recent years, Professor Bettany Hughes explores ancient archaeological sites that shed light on the modern human story of civilisation; championing what ordinary people, through time, can achieve through sheer force of will and inspiration. These are neglected stories from unheard voices in extraordinary, often overlooked places. In this episode, Bettany explores mountainous Albania, the hidden gem of the Balkans once known as the mystical land of Illyria. She journeys to epic fortress towns and breathtaking archaeological sites and encounters a richly diverse history and culture. Bettany visits the ancient city of Butrint, meets remote communities in the spectacular Albanian Alps, discovers the Ottoman town of Gjirokaste?r and goes underground to the secret bunker of former communist dictator Enver Hoxha.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220155000 +0000" stop="20241220165500 +0000" channel="ViasatHistory.ee"><title lang="ee">Vatican - The Timeless City of Popes</title><desc lang="ee">Viasat History. Guided by historians deciphering the Vatican&apos;s rich archives following recent restorations and excavations, the Vatican delivers new untold secrets and reveals a fascinating historical saga.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220165500 +0000" stop="20241220175500 +0000" channel="ViasatHistory.ee"><title lang="ee">The World War: 1914-1945</title><desc lang="ee">Road To World Domination 1941 - 1944. Operation Barbarossa&apos;s endgame does not come to fruition; with the world distracted, Japan launch their attack on Pearl Harbor, forcing American isolationists to join the war in earnest.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220175500 +0000" stop="20241220190000 +0000" channel="ViasatHistory.ee"><title lang="ee">World War II: The Price of Empire</title><desc lang="ee">Documentary series that tells the story of the greatest man made event in history - World War II, from the beginning to an end, using archive footage and testimonies of more than fifty eyewitnesses to the war. Often the story of WWII begins with the rise of the Third Reich in Germany, and is told from 1 September 1939 with Germany&apos;s invasion of Poland. But this story will start earlier, as empires of the east had been in conflict since Japan&apos;s invasion of China in 1937. The wars of east and west fused to become the Second World War, changing the political map of the world.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220190000 +0000" stop="20241220200000 +0000" channel="ViasatHistory.ee"><title lang="ee">The Secret Story of the Knights Templar</title><desc lang="ee">This fascinating docu-series charts the historical journey of the secretive and mysterious Knights Templar. Beginning with their establishment in medieval Europe as a religious-military order, they soon developed into one of the most powerful organisations of the time. But their acquisition of power and influence drew criticism and condemnation from different quarters. Their legacy is still visible today in the shape of impressive castles, villages and abbeys.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220200000 +0000" stop="20241220210000 +0000" channel="ViasatHistory.ee"><title lang="ee">Conquistadors: The Rise and Fall</title><desc lang="ee">The ruthlessly ambitious Hernán Cortés travels deep into the Mexican interior to conquer the Aztecs, one of the greatest empires in the Americas.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220210000 +0000" stop="20241220220500 +0000" channel="ViasatHistory.ee"><title lang="ee">Nazi Killing Fields</title><desc lang="ee">March 1945: a special unit of the SS feels disturbed by wandering forced labourers in the West when their commander orders a massacre; this was a war crime that remained unpunished for decades.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220220500 +0000" stop="20241220231500 +0000" channel="ViasatHistory.ee"><title lang="ee">The Secret Story of the Knights Templar</title><desc lang="ee">This fascinating docu-series charts the historical journey of the secretive and mysterious Knights Templar. Beginning with their establishment in medieval Europe as a religious-military order, they soon developed into one of the most powerful organisations of the time. But their acquisition of power and influence drew criticism and condemnation from different quarters. Their legacy is still visible today in the shape of impressive castles, villages and abbeys.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220231500 +0000" stop="20241221001000 +0000" channel="ViasatHistory.ee"><title lang="ee">Secret Nazi Bases</title><desc lang="ee">The secrecy and discrepancy of the Nazi party during the Second World War, is something that has been shrouded in mystery for a number of decades. Secret Nazi Bases, tries to illustrate the various places where high authoritative members of this dastardly regime, exhibited true &apos;cowardice&apos;. As sinister perpetrators during WWII, we explore and illustrate the various expeditions that figures of the &apos;Third Reich&apos;, had taken to escape judicial punishment. From hidden Bavarian villages in Argentina, to the expansive Nazi base of &quot;Dag Bromberg&quot; in the Polish forest. We&apos;ve put together a compilation that assesses and evaluates, Nazi Base structure and fortification. Providing details of where these bases lie, we excavate and investigate the secret buildings that illustrate Hitler&apos;s ambitions.</desc></programme>
