<programme start="20241220041500 +0000" stop="20241220054500 +0000" channel="ViasatKino.ee"><title lang="ee">The Librarian: Quest for the Spear</title><desc lang="ee">Uber-geek Flynn finally finds a use for his encyclopaedic knowledge of the obscure and esoteric when he&apos;s selected to join a mysterious order of &quot;Librarians&quot;. Assigned the grave responsibility of protecting a collection of mythical artifacts from the forces of evil who, if given the chance, would use the priceless treasures for their nefarious plans, Flynn, along with sexy Amazon bodyguard Nicole journeys to the most exotic, inaccessible and treacherous corners of the earth, but does he have what it takes to be... &quot;The Librarian&quot;?</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220054500 +0000" stop="20241220075000 +0000" channel="ViasatKino.ee"><title lang="ee">Dark Waters</title><desc lang="ee">A tenacious attorney uncovers a dark secret that connects a growing number of unexplained deaths to one of the world&apos;s largest corporations. While trying to expose the truth, he soon finds himself risking his future, his family and his own life.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220075000 +0000" stop="20241220100000 +0000" channel="ViasatKino.ee"><title lang="ee">Million Dollar Baby</title><desc lang="ee">Hilary Swank stars in Clint Eastwood&apos;s film as Maggie Fitzgerald, a waitress who believes she can make it to the top in the female boxing ranks. Much against his will, she persuades ageing trainer Frankie Dunn (Eastwood) to take her on, and with his sidekick Eddie &quot;&quot;Scrap-Iron&quot;&quot; Dupris (Morgan Freeman), he takes her to the top and a title fight. Which is when the film takes a very different turn and Dunn faces guilt and doubts that conflict with his strict Catholic beliefs. The film is an outstanding, riveting drama and it&apos;s no surprise that Swank and Freeman won Oscars for their performances, Eastwood for best director and the film for best picture.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220100000 +0000" stop="20241220115000 +0000" channel="ViasatKino.ee"><title lang="ee">Sommersby</title><desc lang="ee">Jack is arrested and tried for the murder of a local gambler many years ago. As the trial proceeds, Orin becomes convinced the accused is an imposter. He persuades Laurel into attemptig to save the defendant by exposing him as a fraud - which would nullify his claim to his &quot;wife&quot;. Laurel at first goes along with the plan, but then cedes to Jack&apos;s wish that she retract her statement. Once sentenced to death, JAck admits to Laurel that he his Horace Townsend, a former schoolteacher, and that he appropriated her husband&apos;s name fater the real Jack was killed, shortly after killing the gambler. He is hanged as the town finds itself rich, thanks to the sale of the tobacco crop.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220115000 +0000" stop="20241220133500 +0000" channel="ViasatKino.ee"><title lang="ee">Charming the Hearts of Men</title><desc lang="ee">A romantic drama set during the politically charged early 60s where a sophisticated woman returns to her Southern home town and discovers her options are limited yet discrimination is plentiful. With the help of a Congressional ally, she inspires historic legislation which allows opportunities and protections never before afforded to women.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220133500 +0000" stop="20241220152000 +0000" channel="ViasatKino.ee"><title lang="ee">Labor Day</title><desc lang="ee">(2013) 104 mins 12 Kate Winslet, Josh Brolin and Gattlin Griffith star in writer-director Jason Reitman&apos;s drama, adapted from the novel by Joyce Maynard. Winslet plays Adele, divorced and depressed after a string of miscarriages that followed the birth of her only son Henry (Griffith), who is now 13. On a trip to the supermarket, mother and son are accosted by escaped convict Frank (Brolin) who forces them to provide him with refuge at their home. Frank was jailed for the murder of his girlfriend, but he claims it was an accident. Gradually the captor/hostage relationship morphs into something more sympathetic, as Frank becomes a father figure to Henry, and romance blossoms between him and Adele. But although these damaged individuals seem to have formed a harmonious family unit, a planned escape over the border to Canada arouses suspicions...</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220152000 +0000" stop="20241220172000 +0000" channel="ViasatKino.ee"><title lang="ee">The Client</title><desc lang="ee">Based on the bestseller by John Grisham, The Client is a slickly packaged thriller wrapped in fashionable paranoia and tied up with an incongruously heartening moral. Susan Sarandon won an Academy Award nomination for her portrayal of anti-establishment lawyer Reggie Love, whose tough surface hides a heart of pure Jell-O. Fatherless Mark Sway (Brad Renfro) and his younger brother, Ricky (David Speck), live with their beleaguered mother Dianne (Mary-Louise Parker) in a trailer camp near Memphis. They sneak off to play in the nearby woods and witness something terrible. Slick city attorney Romey Clifford (Walter Olkewicz) has come to the woods to commit suicide, and Mark spends a terrifying few minutes in Clifford&apos;s car, listening to him rant about his connection to gangster Barry Muldano (Anthony LaPaglia), who murdered a Senator. Clifford knows where the body is, and would rather die by his own hand than face Muldano. Mark and Ricky escape, but Ricky is taken to the hospital, traumatized and almost comatose. Mark refuses to tell anyone what happened, but the police find Clifford&apos;s body and realize that someone else was in the car. They search for the witness, as do Muldano and his hoods. Pressured by the media, the police and the mob, Mark realizes he needs help and looks for a lawyer. He walks into the office of feisty recovering alcoholic Reggie Love (Sarandon), who can&apos;t resist a hopeless case. Her first task is to protect Mark from flamboyant Federal Attorney Roy Foltrigg (Tommy Lee Jones), who tries to trick Mark into revealing what he knows. Love realizes that Foltrigg is primarily concerned with furthering his own political ambitions, and that unless she can negotiate certain guarantees of protection before he testifies, her client and his family will be killed. After the mob torches the Sways&apos; trailer, Mark hides out with Love, who lost her own children in a bitter custody dispute.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220172000 +0000" stop="20241220190000 +0000" channel="ViasatKino.ee"><title lang="ee">The Perks of Being a Wallflower</title><desc lang="ee">Logan Lerman, Emma Watson and Ezra Miller star in writer-director Stephen Chbosky&apos;s romantic drama. It&apos;s 1991 and Charlie (Lerman) has just started his first year of high school in Pittsburgh. While his bookishness hampers friendship with his fellow freshmen, he&apos;s saved from complete isolation by his empathetic English teacher, Mr Anderson (Paul Rudd), who takes him under his wing. However, Charlie really lucks out when music-obsessed step-siblings Sam (Watson) and Patrick (Miller), who are in their final year, recognise a kindred spirit and take him into their circle of friends. And so begins the year in which Charlie discovers romance, broadens his horizons with regard to sex, sexuality, drink and drugs, and confronts some of the darker episodes from his past. Also starring Mae Whitman as the punk who takes a shine to Charlie; Adam Hagenbuch as the lad who introduces him to some illicit delights; and Johnny Simmons as Brad, Patrick&apos;s boyfriend.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220190000 +0000" stop="20241220204000 +0000" channel="ViasatKino.ee"><title lang="ee">Hard Candy</title><desc lang="ee">Hayley, a 14-year-old girl, meets Geoff, a 32-year-old fashion photographer, on the Internet. They make arrangements to meet in person in a coffee shop and she winds up going back to his house. There is a game of cat and mouse, with surprising results.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220204000 +0000" stop="20241220222000 +0000" channel="ViasatKino.ee"><title lang="ee">Bruiser</title><desc lang="ee">After years of being tread upon and cheated on, a man awakens to find his face has a been replaced by a blank, white mask.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220222000 +0000" stop="20241221001000 +0000" channel="ViasatKino.ee"><title lang="ee">Crossing Over</title><desc lang="ee">Crossing Over (2009) is an independent crime drama directed by Wayne Kramer and starring Harrison Ford and Ray Liotta. The immigrants of different nationalities are struggling to achieve legal status in Los Angeles. All of their lives connect in some way and in order to find asylum and get the green card, they have to face all the difficulties of obtaining legal status, the clash of cultures and feel the contrast between the American dream and the reality that they find.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241221001000 +0000" stop="20241221020000 +0000" channel="ViasatKino.ee"><title lang="ee">Stonehearst Asylum</title><desc lang="ee">Ben Kingsley and Kate Beckinsale star in director Brad Anderson&apos;s adaptation of Edgar Allan Poe&apos;s Gothic-thriller Eliza Graves. The year is 1899, and medical school graduate Edward Newgate (Jim Sturgess) is the newest clinical recruit at Stonehearst: a mental asylum for the privileged and wealthy. He&apos;s keen to gain as much experience as possible, but he becomes increasingly concerned as the techniques of his superior, Dr Silas Lamb (Kingsley), get increasingly unconventional. Despite growing apprehension about the legitimacy of the establishment and the malpractice taking place within its walls, Edward stays at Stonehearst, where he becomes infatuated with a captivating and ostensibly sane patient called Eliza (Beckinsale). But Stonehearst&apos;s secrets are far darker than Edward initially feared... Also starring Brendan Gleeson, Michael Caine and David Thewlis. First screening on Channel 4 (previously seen on Film4).</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241221020000 +0000" stop="20241221032500 +0000" channel="ViasatKino.ee"><title lang="ee">Enchanted Kingdom</title><desc lang="ee">This absolutely beautiful documentary on our World, its mystical beauty and miracles including slow motion footage of nature, animals, seasons, new life and daily beauties I&apos;ve never seen nor imagined existed. The photography is sensational. The animal behaviour shown is incredible, beautiful and humorous. Never been a fan of nature documentaries, this blew me away.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241221032500 +0000" stop="20241221051000 +0000" channel="ViasatKino.ee"><title lang="ee">Charming the Hearts of Men</title><desc lang="ee">A romantic drama set during the politically charged early 60s where a sophisticated woman returns to her Southern home town and discovers her options are limited yet discrimination is plentiful. With the help of a Congressional ally, she inspires historic legislation which allows opportunities and protections never before afforded to women.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220041500 +0000" stop="20241220054500 +0000" channel="ViasatKino.lv"><title lang="lv">The Librarian: Quest for the Spear</title><desc lang="lv">Uber-geek Flynn finally finds a use for his encyclopaedic knowledge of the obscure and esoteric when he&apos;s selected to join a mysterious order of &quot;Librarians&quot;. Assigned the grave responsibility of protecting a collection of mythical artifacts from the forces of evil who, if given the chance, would use the priceless treasures for their nefarious plans, Flynn, along with sexy Amazon bodyguard Nicole journeys to the most exotic, inaccessible and treacherous corners of the earth, but does he have what it takes to be... &quot;The Librarian&quot;?</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220054500 +0000" stop="20241220075000 +0000" channel="ViasatKino.lv"><title lang="lv">Dark Waters</title><desc lang="lv">A tenacious attorney uncovers a dark secret that connects a growing number of unexplained deaths to one of the world&apos;s largest corporations. While trying to expose the truth, he soon finds himself risking his future, his family and his own life.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220075000 +0000" stop="20241220100000 +0000" channel="ViasatKino.lv"><title lang="lv">Million Dollar Baby</title><desc lang="lv">Hilary Swank stars in Clint Eastwood&apos;s film as Maggie Fitzgerald, a waitress who believes she can make it to the top in the female boxing ranks. Much against his will, she persuades ageing trainer Frankie Dunn (Eastwood) to take her on, and with his sidekick Eddie &quot;&quot;Scrap-Iron&quot;&quot; Dupris (Morgan Freeman), he takes her to the top and a title fight. Which is when the film takes a very different turn and Dunn faces guilt and doubts that conflict with his strict Catholic beliefs. The film is an outstanding, riveting drama and it&apos;s no surprise that Swank and Freeman won Oscars for their performances, Eastwood for best director and the film for best picture.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220100000 +0000" stop="20241220115000 +0000" channel="ViasatKino.lv"><title lang="lv">Sommersby</title><desc lang="lv">Jack is arrested and tried for the murder of a local gambler many years ago. As the trial proceeds, Orin becomes convinced the accused is an imposter. He persuades Laurel into attemptig to save the defendant by exposing him as a fraud - which would nullify his claim to his &quot;wife&quot;. Laurel at first goes along with the plan, but then cedes to Jack&apos;s wish that she retract her statement. Once sentenced to death, JAck admits to Laurel that he his Horace Townsend, a former schoolteacher, and that he appropriated her husband&apos;s name fater the real Jack was killed, shortly after killing the gambler. He is hanged as the town finds itself rich, thanks to the sale of the tobacco crop.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220115000 +0000" stop="20241220133500 +0000" channel="ViasatKino.lv"><title lang="lv">Charming the Hearts of Men</title><desc lang="lv">A romantic drama set during the politically charged early 60s where a sophisticated woman returns to her Southern home town and discovers her options are limited yet discrimination is plentiful. With the help of a Congressional ally, she inspires historic legislation which allows opportunities and protections never before afforded to women.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220133500 +0000" stop="20241220152000 +0000" channel="ViasatKino.lv"><title lang="lv">Labor Day</title><desc lang="lv">(2013) 104 mins 12 Kate Winslet, Josh Brolin and Gattlin Griffith star in writer-director Jason Reitman&apos;s drama, adapted from the novel by Joyce Maynard. Winslet plays Adele, divorced and depressed after a string of miscarriages that followed the birth of her only son Henry (Griffith), who is now 13. On a trip to the supermarket, mother and son are accosted by escaped convict Frank (Brolin) who forces them to provide him with refuge at their home. Frank was jailed for the murder of his girlfriend, but he claims it was an accident. Gradually the captor/hostage relationship morphs into something more sympathetic, as Frank becomes a father figure to Henry, and romance blossoms between him and Adele. But although these damaged individuals seem to have formed a harmonious family unit, a planned escape over the border to Canada arouses suspicions...</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220152000 +0000" stop="20241220172000 +0000" channel="ViasatKino.lv"><title lang="lv">The Client</title><desc lang="lv">Based on the bestseller by John Grisham, The Client is a slickly packaged thriller wrapped in fashionable paranoia and tied up with an incongruously heartening moral. Susan Sarandon won an Academy Award nomination for her portrayal of anti-establishment lawyer Reggie Love, whose tough surface hides a heart of pure Jell-O. Fatherless Mark Sway (Brad Renfro) and his younger brother, Ricky (David Speck), live with their beleaguered mother Dianne (Mary-Louise Parker) in a trailer camp near Memphis. They sneak off to play in the nearby woods and witness something terrible. Slick city attorney Romey Clifford (Walter Olkewicz) has come to the woods to commit suicide, and Mark spends a terrifying few minutes in Clifford&apos;s car, listening to him rant about his connection to gangster Barry Muldano (Anthony LaPaglia), who murdered a Senator. Clifford knows where the body is, and would rather die by his own hand than face Muldano. Mark and Ricky escape, but Ricky is taken to the hospital, traumatized and almost comatose. Mark refuses to tell anyone what happened, but the police find Clifford&apos;s body and realize that someone else was in the car. They search for the witness, as do Muldano and his hoods. Pressured by the media, the police and the mob, Mark realizes he needs help and looks for a lawyer. He walks into the office of feisty recovering alcoholic Reggie Love (Sarandon), who can&apos;t resist a hopeless case. Her first task is to protect Mark from flamboyant Federal Attorney Roy Foltrigg (Tommy Lee Jones), who tries to trick Mark into revealing what he knows. Love realizes that Foltrigg is primarily concerned with furthering his own political ambitions, and that unless she can negotiate certain guarantees of protection before he testifies, her client and his family will be killed. After the mob torches the Sways&apos; trailer, Mark hides out with Love, who lost her own children in a bitter custody dispute.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220172000 +0000" stop="20241220190000 +0000" channel="ViasatKino.lv"><title lang="lv">The Perks of Being a Wallflower</title><desc lang="lv">Logan Lerman, Emma Watson and Ezra Miller star in writer-director Stephen Chbosky&apos;s romantic drama. It&apos;s 1991 and Charlie (Lerman) has just started his first year of high school in Pittsburgh. While his bookishness hampers friendship with his fellow freshmen, he&apos;s saved from complete isolation by his empathetic English teacher, Mr Anderson (Paul Rudd), who takes him under his wing. However, Charlie really lucks out when music-obsessed step-siblings Sam (Watson) and Patrick (Miller), who are in their final year, recognise a kindred spirit and take him into their circle of friends. And so begins the year in which Charlie discovers romance, broadens his horizons with regard to sex, sexuality, drink and drugs, and confronts some of the darker episodes from his past. Also starring Mae Whitman as the punk who takes a shine to Charlie; Adam Hagenbuch as the lad who introduces him to some illicit delights; and Johnny Simmons as Brad, Patrick&apos;s boyfriend.</desc></programme>
