<programme start="20241220163000 +0000" stop="20241220172000 +0000" channel="ViasatNature.lv"><title lang="lv">River Monsters</title><desc lang="lv">Wildlife documentary series presented by Jeremy Wade. Jeremy takes on Africa&apos;s wild Zambezi River to unmask an invisible predator that is dragging fishermen to their deaths. Crocodiles and hippos have taken dozens of victims in plain view, but it seems there is another monstrous beast stalking these deep and turbulent waters. Locals speak of the Mazunda - but what can this sinister, child-devouring creature be?.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220172000 +0000" stop="20241220181000 +0000" channel="ViasatNature.lv"><title lang="lv">Wildlife Rescue Australia</title><desc lang="lv">Manda the Wombat. Manda the wombat has problems with her teeth, Cher the squirrel glider possum won&apos;t survive unless Dr Bree can repair her eye, and MacGyver the Eastern long-necked turtle has been hit by a car.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220181000 +0000" stop="20241220190000 +0000" channel="ViasatNature.lv"><title lang="lv">Nature&apos;s Fast Attacks</title><desc lang="lv">Stealth Hunters. In the battle between predator and prey, we explore how deception and speed can often be the difference between life and death; even some of the fastest hunters use stealth to trick their prey.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220190000 +0000" stop="20241220195000 +0000" channel="ViasatNature.lv"><title lang="lv">Nature&apos;s Ultimate Survivors</title><desc lang="lv">From torpedo-like birds to astonishing symbiotic partnerships, these aquatic marvels have evolved to thrive in the harsh environments of Earth&apos;s vast waterways.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220195000 +0000" stop="20241220204500 +0000" channel="ViasatNature.lv"><title lang="lv">Wild Battleground</title><desc lang="lv">Forest Fights. Tropical rainforests are the most diverse ecosystems on the planet; that means intense competition. Crocodiles in the mangrove forests of Borneo are drawn to the rich variety of species on offer.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220204500 +0000" stop="20241220213500 +0000" channel="ViasatNature.lv"><title lang="lv">Wild Battleground</title><desc lang="lv">Water Wars. From rivers to oceans, water wars rewrite the rules of conflict; gravity has no meaning underwater. Weird and wonderful creatures of the reef terrorise each other as they battle for an inch of space.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220213500 +0000" stop="20241220223000 +0000" channel="ViasatNature.lv"><title lang="lv">Extreme Snakes</title><desc lang="lv">Africa&apos;s diverse snake species have surprisingly adapted to dominate each corner of one of Earth&apos;s wildest terrains, evolving to thrive in the myriad of habitats of this biodiverse continent.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220223000 +0000" stop="20241220232000 +0000" channel="ViasatNature.lv"><title lang="lv">Malawi Wildlife Rescue</title><desc lang="lv">Strap in for Dr. Amanda&apos;s risky attempt to collar a wild roan antelope. Later, chase down blue monkey Indigo while unrest ensues among the vervets. Examine an eagle owl with bumblefoot and say adieu to Sheila the croc, who&apos;s headed back to the wild.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241220232000 +0000" stop="20241221000000 +0000" channel="ViasatNature.lv"><title lang="lv">The Bizarre Pet Vets</title><desc lang="lv">Nature documentary - Ep. 2. Dr James treats a Boyd&apos;s Forest dragon at the clinic, Dr Shane treats a carpet python called Red, and Dr Catherine sees an emergency case; sun conure parakeet Tequila is in a lot of pain.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241221000000 +0000" stop="20241221005000 +0000" channel="ViasatNature.lv"><title lang="lv">Wildest Survival</title><desc lang="lv">Dive into the breathtaking world of nature as we explore the lives of our planet&apos;s weirdest and wildest creatures, learning how they have adapted to their surroundings in order to survive. Some of these remarkable species have lived on our planet for thousands, if not millions, of years. We reveal how these animals have evolved through the generations to remain a thriving species. With the current, devastating environmental plight, Wildest Survival showcases the importance of these wonderful species, showing what we could lose if human habits remain unaltered.</desc></programme>
<programme start="20241221005000 +0000" stop="20241221013500 +0000" channel="ViasatNature.lv"><title lang="lv">The Yorkshire Vet</title><desc lang="lv">A heartwarming documentary series that follows the work of former Herriot Trainee Peter Wright and his partner. The show focuses on the declining veterinary specialism of small animals or livestock, and follows the pair of vets on visit to clients in remote farm locations as they care for animals in the rural communities of North Yorkshire. The show also benefits from the beautiful backgrounds and stunning scenery of the Yorkshire Dales and North York Moors, adding an extra dimension to this veterinary show.</desc></programme>
